I swear to God there’s no one like you

To dard yoon mujh pe aaye
Tere siwa koyi bhi aarzu na ho

I wish that I could take any pain you suffer upon myself
That I should have no desire but you

‘Ishq tere ch tar main jawaan
Saari duniya ton lad main jawaan

That I should float to the shore in your love

snippet.textDisplay: A wonderful wonderful composition Shuja Haider! This is my ultimate favourite of the Coke studio.  this is the first ever number I watched of Coke studio Pak  n I can't tell u how bowled over I was. Sumone told me about coke studio pak n mentioned that its one of the best musical program & I absolutly second that. U ve composed it so beautifully  that one goes into a diff world altogether . For me Music is such a powerful source of inspiration independent of language n Religion.  My mother use to say she used to find ultimate peace in music  rather than in prayers when she was in pain or deep sadness. N she believed that the real people of God are those musicians who thru their music gives so much pleasure n peace to people. N I so much believe in this theory. I hope u read this shuja haider coz ur music brings so much positive energy n solace to people like me. My mother would be loved your Allahu Akbar & Baaware so much . but am sure she must be listening sumwhr up there n sending u her Ashirwaad .Bless U n a warm hug .
